<!--
  SPEC.md — Project specification template for dev-workflow ingest.

  This skeleton mirrors the 4-phase output of `/vault:from-spec` exactly.
  Fill each subsection with project facts. Leave subsections empty (or
  delete them) if they don't apply — `from-spec` skips empty sections.

  The bootstrap block below tells Claude Code (and humans) how to wire
  the project to dev-workflow. Keep it on top — it is read before any
  ingest happens.
-->

> **Bootstrap order (run once, in this order):**
> 1. `git init && dev-workflow init` — installs CLAUDE.md, `.claude/`, `.mcp.json`, copies commands and agents.
> 2. `/vault:from-spec docs/SPEC.md` — populates `.dev-vault/{stack,conventions,knowledge,gameplan}.md` from this file.
> 3. `dev-workflow task list` then `/workflow:dev "<phase 1 task>"` — start the first implementation cycle.
>
> Keep this SPEC.md project-pure: no slash commands, vault rules, or engram protocol here. Those live in CLAUDE.md (delivered by `dev-workflow init`) under `/vault:upgrade` control.

